window.bookSummaryJSON = "Rainbow’s back and broker than before.<br>She’s learned a lot about life over the years of beauty pageants and investigative journalism, but she’s about to find out that, like marrying for money, when you take a job you don’t love, you earn every penny — and then some.<br>Out of work and in debt up to her diamond studs, Rainbow is desperate for cash and accepts a lowly PR job. There are many reasons to not love Dr. Regina Fell, starting with the punishing workouts and lukewarm water as their only “refreshment.” But the worst is the way she treats her family. She makes the Wicked Witch of the West seem like a fairy godmother. And her personal assistant might as well wear a rubber mat on her back.<br>Rainbow has just made up her mind to quit when Dr. Fell turns up dead! Once again, Rainbow must use all her wiles (including her wily pet ferret) to save the innocent from winding up behind bars, not to mention make sure the guilt party doesn't get away with murder!<br>Fans of Gina Lamanna, Maddie Day and Laura Levine will adore this funny, sweaty, but not-too-scary cozy mystery.<br>**Formerly titled: Pop Goes the Workout Wench**"; 
